CatDescriptText: Mr. Willie Chestnut, 230 Renfrew Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Which do you think people give priority recognition to, the acquisition of money or achievement?" answer reads: "People recognize money instead of achievement."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Willie Chestnut, wearing striped coat, striped cap, and light colored plaid button down collared shirt, standing in front of multicolor flecked stone wall, window on left
